    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3

    ValueWithAttributes OriginalIssueAttributes

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3:OriginalIssueAttributes

      • Description

        Provides information about the original document on which the reissue is based.

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<OriginalIssueAttributes checkInhibitor="CheckDigit" coupons="Example String Value Example String Value Example String Value" issueDate="1999-07-16" issueIATA="32938473829" issuePlace="Boston" paymentForm="Credit card" ticketNumber="238473638474" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/finance/v3"/>

      Example JSON

      {
  "OriginalIssueAttributes" : {
    "value" : null,
    "ticketNumber" : "238473638474",
    "issuePlace" : "Boston",
    "issueDate" : "1999-07-16",
    "issueIATA" : "32938473829",
    "paymentForm" : "Credit card",
    "checkInhibitor" : "CheckDigit",
    "coupons" : [ "Example", "String", "Value", "Example", "String", "Value", "Example", "String", "Value" ]
  }
}

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        ticketNumber
        The original ticket number in a series if reissuances.
        Details
        Type TicketNumber
        Example Value 238473638474
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        issuePlace
        Place where the original ticket was issued.
        Details
        Type StringTiny
        Example Value Boston
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        issueDate
        Date when the original ticket was issued.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:date
        Example Value 1999-07-16
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        issueIATA
        IATA office number, which issued original ticket.
        Details
        Type StringTiny
        Example Value 32938473829
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        paymentForm
        Payment type for the original ticket.
        Details
        Type StringTiny
        Example Value Credit card
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        checkInhibitor
        When present, indicates that the check digit of the ticket number or the interline agreement do not need to be checked.
        Details
        Type CheckInhibitor_Enum
        Example Value CheckDigit
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        coupons
        Gives a list of references to coupon numbers of the ticket which will be taken for payment.
        Details
        Type Coupons
        Example Value Example String Value Example String Value Example String Value
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
